<h2 id="supporting-accessibility-and-inclusion">Supporting accessibility and inclusion</h2>
<p>Generally, digital channels can be made accessible through assistive technology. Letters sent through NHS Notify are available in accessible formats including easy read and braille.</p>
<p><a href="https://notify.nhs.uk/using-nhs-notify/accessible-formats" title="External website">Read more about accessible formats when sending messages through NHS Notify</a>.</p>
<p>Your message should use language that is inclusive and respectful.</p>
<p><a href="https://service-manual.nhs.uk/content/inclusive-content" title="External website">Read about inclusive content when writing for the NHS</a>.</p>
<p>All NHS web pages and content should follow the principles of <a href="https://service-manual.nhs.uk/design-system/changes-to-design-system-wcag-2-2" title="External website">Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) as set out in the NHS Digital Service Manual</a>.</p>

